1. Introduction

Office workers are one of the most valuable customers to coffee shops. They usually order take outs and thus do not sit for long
hours with a cup of coffee, which is usually the case for students. Furthermore, they tend to be regular customers. Unless the taste of 
coffee is really bad, most will continue to go to the nearby coffee shop to get caffeinated when they are tired in the morning or
after lunch. For those who are thinking about opening up a coffee shop in Boston, an ideal location may be where there are many companies 
but not many coffee shops nearby. Let's try to come up with an ideal location for a new coffee shop in Boston!
